{"title":"April Fools’ joke results in Japanese firm making a beige ’80s throwback PC case","link":"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/11/big-beige-80s-pc-case-started-out-as-a-joke-but-its-becoming-real-in-japan/","date":1731948083000,"content":"<p>Putting out a joke product on April Fools' Day can sometimes be a clever way to quietly gauge the reaction to a wild idea without having to really commit to it.</p>\n<p>Nerdish purveyor ThinkGeek did this a few times with <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2007/10/thinkgeek-8-bit-tie-ships/\">the 8-bit tie</a> and the <a href=\"https://www.wired.com/2009/04/tauntaun-sleepi/\">Tauntaun sleeping bag</a>. <em>Pokemon Go</em> crystallized in some ways from <a href=\"https://www.cnet.com/tech/gaming/googles-april-fools-prank-puts-pokemon-in-the-real-world/\">a Google Maps joke</a>. And just recently, PC case-maker SilverStone has decided that so many people were into <a href=\"https://x.com/SilverStoneJP/status/1641817673616216065/photo/1\">its beige-tastic FLP01 case idea</a>, tossed onto X (formerly Twitter) late on March 31 Tokyo time, that it will now release it in early 2025 in Japan for the USD equivalent of $130.</p>\n<figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone1-1024x768.jpeg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone1-1024x768.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone1-640x480.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone1-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone1-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone1-980x735.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone1-1440x1080.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone1.jpeg 2048w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      Proof of life for the off-white box that sits on a desk.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          SilverStone\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone2-1024x1365.jpeg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone2-1024x1365.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone2-640x853.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone2-768x1024.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone2-1152x1536.jpeg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone2-980x1307.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone2-1440x1920.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/silverstone2.jpeg 1536w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      The SLP-01, as configured by SilverStone at the Expo 2024.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          SilverStone\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii_try2-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"Top 3/4 view of the SLP-01 case, with PSU and graphics card showing.\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii_try2-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii_try2-640x427.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii_try2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii_try2-980x653.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii_try2.jpg 1200w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      3/4-view of the SLP-01 case shown off at Expo 2024, captured by Ascii.jp.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n                      <a href=\"https://ascii.jp/elem/000/004/235/4235230/\" target=\"_blank\">\n          \n          Ascii.jp\n\n                      </a>\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii2_try2-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"Front view of the SLP-01, with an Asus disc drive tray ejected from the front.\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii2_try2-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii2_try2-640x427.jpg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii2_try2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii2_try2-980x653.jpg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/sstone_ascii2_try2.jpg 1200w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      The 5-1/4 drive bays are fake, but the ability to use an honest-to-goodness CD drive is real.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n                      <a href=\"https://ascii.jp/elem/000/004/235/4235230/\" target=\"_blank\">\n          \n          Ascii.jp\n\n                      </a>\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n  \n<p>As shown off at <a href=\"https://ascii.jp/elem/000/004/235/4235230/\">SilverStone's Expo 2024 show in Akihbara last weekend</a> (and spotted <a href=\"https://www.tomshardware.com/pc-components/pc-cases/retro-beige-pc-case-goes-from-april-fools-joke-to-retail-silverstones-sleeper-pc-with-modern-internals-ships-in-q1-2025\">on Tom's Hardware</a>), the FLP-01 is a combination of simulacrum and serious, with heavy <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PC-98\">NEC PC-9800 homage</a>. It has fake 5.25-inch floppy blanks, but they cover real optical disc drive and button/port modules. At SilverStone's Japan Expo, the firm packed a GeForce RTX 4060 Ti, Intel Core Ultra 7 256K CPU, and full-size ATX motherboard and PSU. There are, of course, power and disk activity LEDs on the front. As displayed, SilverStone's demo unit had three intake fans and plenty of room for whatever else you could pack in here.</p><p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/11/big-beige-80s-pc-case-started-out-as-a-joke-but-its-becoming-real-in-japan/\">Read full article</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/11/big-beige-80s-pc-case-started-out-as-a-joke-but-its-becoming-real-in-japan/#comments\">Comments</a></p>","author":"Kevin Purdy","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0ddf6e8923e49262a7894cfd77962733e43fbcc565a103b48373820b310636","entryHash":"fdc1834c3a90d0eba5445761d866f626c19433620e46cebd28a1d645865a967a","category":"Tech"}